theorem Topology.dense_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) → Dense (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Dense] at *
  -- `hDense` tells us that `closure A = univ`.
  have h_cl : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Rewriting with `h_cl` shows that `closure (closure A) = univ`.
  simpa [closure_closure, h_cl] using
    (rfl : closure (closure (A : Set X)) = closure (A : Set X))

theorem Dense.closure_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : Dense (A : Set X)) : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro _; simp
  · intro _; exact h x
